Great Viet place downtown Boise. I ordered their Rice vermicelli bowl with grilled pork and crispy egg rolls (bún thịt nướng chả giò) and my sister got the spicy noodle soup (bún bò Huế) with the Vietnamese meat cuts. My noodle bowl was fantastic! I chomped down on it to the very last bit. My sister's noodle soup was not what we expected, though. There was...turmeric? I guessed, in the soup (which is not what we're familiar with, even back home in Nam.) It could be the regional difference for all we know. The staff was great and the price is darn good for downtown Boise! Highly recommend!

I order a second entree to go sometimes just so I can have more leftovers the next day.  The space is a little crowded and a tight fit especially during the lunch and dinner rush, and there's often a line. If you have a few minutes to wait (or call ahead for take out) it's so worth it! I ordered vegetable phó and while the rice noodles and ingredients were good and fresh, the veggie broth was horribly sweet and killed the natural flavors. It permeated everything. Maybe you might like that? It ruined it for me and I couldn't wait to come home for Pacific Rim Vietnamese. Otherwise I think the atmosphere and service were very good.

Also the meat in it tasted a bit off, not obviously so but you'd get a bad bite here and there.  A weird thing was that the noodles were all different lengths, some were normal but a lot were between 1 - 3 inches long. Normally that's not a problem but in addition to the funky meat and overly sweet broth, it really felt like you were eating someone else's unfinished bowl that they tried to pass off as a fresh one.  I seriously hope that's not the case but even so this has to be the worst pho I've ever tried.

Had the shrimp pho. It was a valiant contender, but my heart was really with my appetizer, their absolutely amazing spring rolls. I'm in love with them. If they served a plate of fifteen, I'd buy that aaaalllll day.
Not bad, never had pho before

The phó was lacking in taste and the broth had no flavor and service was okay but could've been better... And my parents can agree with what I'm saying. It had been a while but hopefully they've improved since my last visit, then I'll give it another try.
My husband and I were looking for a vegan friendly place in Boise and stumbled across Pho Nouveau. They had several good vegan options, and the food, drinks and service were all excellent.
The food is excellent. The atmosphere is pleasant.
The BEST bun bo hue! Huge portions, excellent food. The service is lacking, but the food makes up for it.
Delicious pho and fast service.
One of my favorite restaurants downtown! Fresh meat.
Fun menu
Noodles with pork and spring rolls - light and refreshing but also quite filling. Pho was pleasant, nothing extraordinary. Nice place to stop in for a quick lunch.

This was my first time at Pho Nouveau since I was visiting friends in Boise, but my whole family was happy to find a good Vietnamese restaurant since we all love pho.  We were not disappointed; both the pho and bun were great. The only complaint I would have would be the wait, but they were packed sure to a convention in town, so that's no negative reflection on the staff.
We eat here at least once a week the food is great the spring roll is awesome and the pho soup is great..Great place to eat.

Spring rolls were good. I had the Pho but didn't like it. This was due to my own taste buds and does not in any way reflect their cooking. The rest of my group (we had 6 people total), all really liked their food and the place had excellent staff and drinks available. It is rather expensive for my budget but the prices are more than reasonable for the amount of food that you are served.  I am here on my annual trip to visit friends but it has become one of the places that they want to return to. And one of them has declared it, "My favorite new restaurant" and intends to go back in the next few months as budget allows.

One of my new favorite spots downtown. The food is flavorful, fairly priced, and the menu is large enough for everyone in your group to find something they would like. My favorite dish is definitely the beef pho. The space is really small though so if your group is more than 2 people you may want to get their a little before the lunch rush.
Great appetizers!  The crab Rangoons were the best I have ever had! Everything we have ordered in our numerous visits has been amazing!
Low key and very nice place to eat. Staff is friendly and food is great.
The Pho is the best in Boise. I've never tried anything else on the menu because it's always so good.

If you've ever had real pho from Vietnam, this place will not satisfy. If you're fine with an Americanized version, you'll probably think this is pretty good. We felt terrible after eating here though, which makes me wonder if they use MSG.
Pretty great Pho!
Best pho ever! The staff are welcoming and friendly. The pho and pork taste so good! It's is by far the best pork I've ever eaten. I wish I could give this place a thousand stars!
Yummy
The pho is tasty.
Favorite place to get pho, especially on a cold day.
Really good bun bo hue. I've tried it at many Vietnamese restaurants around Idaho and theirs is the best. Pork and crispy spring rolls is also extremely tasty.

Pho in the name thought they would be better.  No tripe, tendon, brisket.  Plain Jane pho, so I opted for something else.  Beef and chicken.  How could u mess that up?   They did.  Over cooked.  Not only that over cook then it was cold.  Would not recommend.  Only one waitress.  Give her props only good thing about this place.  She is a good worker.  All around bad.  10.5 for a bowl of beef pho...$1 extra for meatballs.  Wow, high price bad pho.

I give the food 5 stars so far, but I don't like any of the drink options, but I'm odd that way. I totally dig the freshness of the produce! Keep up the yummy food and as I tell every business, always try to get sustainable products:)
fantastic 👌 service is spot on and food is PHOnomenal!
I love Vietnamese food and this place has pretty good tasting stuff.
Best pho in Boise valley
I've only had the pho but it's pretty good and it's a comfortable lunch environment.
American style dishes and good pho!

Amazing food!!  One of my favorite restaurants in town.  Everything is fresh...The Pho, Fresh Rolls, Bahn Hoi, Chicken Curry, Rice dishes...you can't go wrong!  I have eaten here dozens of times and have never had a bad experience!
We had the Grilled Pork And Crispy Spring Roll On Rice Noodles and Pho 🍲. Both dishes were amazing!
Good pho, haven't tried anything else. Service is pretty quick
Great Pho in an intimate atmosphere.

My wife loves this place, so I've eaten here several times, but their limited menu doesn't do much for me.  The food is good quality, nice atmosphere, good service, friendly knowledgeable staff.  A good experience overall.

A wonderful experience.  My first Vietnamese food experience and it was wonderful.  Spring rolls and Banh Hoi were amazing.  Great location, calm atmosphere and a good wait staff.  Highly recommended!
Love Pho Nouveau and this place makes some great traditional broth. They have some good vegetarian dishes on the menu as well. Everything is so fresh and they accept takeout orders.
pho was excellent. we were seated and served quickly, but it also got busy through lunch so the group I was with was rushed out.
Loved it.  Will be going back soon.

Poor service. One waitress working hard, ours was too busy talking with her friends to check back or refill drinks.  Food was pretty good, loved the taste and quality.  Value was on the low side for the size of the portions.  Atmosphere was quaint, the furnishings were appropriate, but not highly comfortable.  Cleanliness was a challenge.  Food encrusted on the provided fork. Otherwise appeared clean.
Can't go wrong with Pho, alway testy every time I stop by for a bowl of Pho. Lunch menu is pretty good and affordable. Good service and clean place.
Great spicy beef bowl. Great broth, not watered down like other places.
Good pho at a reasonable price. Right in the heart of down town.

Amazing service, amazing food, maybe a tiny bit pricey, but hey, I had a gift card so like I care. Love ya guys, appreciate ya guys. Have a super nice day ya nice lovely people. Oh i got a joke! this place is Pho-cking good! haha! get it! it's not a swear word though! besides the point, come to Pho; great place great food great service.

Good food terrible service.  Unfortunately this is one of the few places in Boise to get Pho.  On two occassions in a row I've ordered food and they've forgotten to put the order in. The funny thing is that the place isn't that big.  My girlfriend and I just ordered food and sat for 40 minutes with no one coming to check for water refills. After we realized that we had been waiting for quite some time I called the attention of the server and they told me that they completely forgot to put the order in and that the kitchen was closed. Keep in mind that there were only three tables that were occupied.  The server then proceeded to offer us a laughable $10 for waiting nearly 40 minutes (that's 80 minutes of life between the two of us) of wasting our time. and then finally offered us two meals after being corrected by another server.  If you do go in make sure to speak up when your waiters are helping other tables to give them a reminder that you still exist and that you plan on giving money for their service. Because they certainly don't seem to value your time.  Worst customer service experience I've ever had.

After moving here from Seattle I was disappointed in the lack of good Pho. I was hesitant to try Pho Nouveau because I thought they would try to be different or take a "new" approach. I'm glad I was wrong! My son and I enjoy their Pho and either dine in or order take out once per week. It's dependably good. When we get sick I come in for just the broth to drink and they have it in 3 sizes. The one thing I wish they had was delivery since parking for take out can be difficult!
My husband and I eat here at least once a month! Great service and GREAT PHO! It's a little small so call ahead on the weekends.
I came here without any expectations of what was here, just a random stop.  It was great, the servers were great since I had no idea what to order.  I loved my meal.  Highly recommend. B
An easily overlooked Vietnamese establishment in downtown Boise complete with outside dining. They can get kind of crowded here in time so just be patient and enjoy the food.

Ok food, poor service. Two of the three food items we wanted to order were not available. After we ordered, it took 50 minutes to get the appetizer and another 5 minutes before our food was served.  During the meal, our waitress bumped into our table, which caused a bit of sauce to spill onto my shirt. She also didn't notice that we were out of rice to go with a spicy chicken dish until I got up to ask for extra rice.  At the end of the meal, I asked if we could have the appetizer comped since it was 50 minutes before we got it. Our waitress told us that this was because she asked us if we wanted all the food when it was ready, and we said yes... I responded that no, I did not mean to indicate that I wanted to wait 50 minutes before having the appetizer. She shouted in response, "We are a family owned restaurant, so I can't comp food, but I'll just take it out of my money." Another waiter came over. He apologized, saying that he did not know what all happened but had removed the appetizer from the bill.  I go to restaurants 3-5 times a week. In the last three years, I never asked for a part of my meal to be comped, but in this case, felt that it would make me feel a little better about the service. The waitress's reaction to my request confirmed that it really was the worst service I had had in the last few years.  On a side note... I had tried Pho Nouveau two years ago, when I ordered takeout. The container with my soup spilled all over inside the bag. The remaining soup did not taste very authentic. I had avoided Pho Nouveau since then, but had decided to give the place another chance tonight, since I really like Vietnamese food.  Regarding the confusions about whether I wanted "all my food when it was ready" - It seems like most restaurants will either start all of your food at the same time, and serve the appetizer and meal to you as soon as they are ready. Or sometimes they make your appetizer, wait for you to get close to finishing, then start your meal. I would have assumed that she was asking which option I preferred, and by answering "when it's ready", I was saying to start all of the food, and bring out each plate as soon as it's ready. In any case, I'm not sure why she would have thought anyone would want to wait 50 minutes before getting an appetizer.
I have seen hit or miss reviews...but I have never had anything but a very great time here. The food is always really good!

I ordered crispy spring rolls and Grilled Pork & Crispy Spring Roll on Rice Noodles (bun thit cha gio).  While the pork and shrimp (I asked them to add shrimp to the noodle dish) were delicately spiced and very good, the fish sauce served for dipping was extremely pungent and did not taste like the fish sauce I've been served in authentic Vietnamese establishments in the past.  I could not eat it.  The crispy spring rolls had too many noodles in them, were dry, and had little flavor - especially when they serve this dish with the fish dipping sauce - again overwhelmingly pungent and inedible.  It's too bad, because I had an incredible craving that I was unable to satisfy.
Really love their noodle dishes.  Pork, spring rolls, and shrimp are always tasty.  Always had decent service here...nice wait staff.

Delicious pho!  I had it with all the herbs and without spiciness, but my husband chose to add in spicy.  We were both delighted.  We also had a Vietnamese crepe for an appetizer, and it looked really weird but tasted awesome.  We will definitely be hitting this restaurant again.

Pho flavor was quite authentic, though the selection (of pho) was very limited. Almost every table ordered pho. I would love it to come with bigger size portion. I agree with a previous review that the flavor was a bit strong. Decoration …
Always packed for lunch, small restaurant.  Quaint. Pretty good food but nothing special,  shrimp were overcooked.

Yuck.  The curry was awful.  It had frozen peas and carrots as its veggies and mangled chicken meat. From the bed by the bathroom (and the children’s bikes and toys), it looks like some lives here.  With so many better places to eat, I won't come back.

My wife and I are from Portland where there are a ton of great Vietnamese restaurants to choose from.  We have been a bit disappointed at the lack of really good, authentic Vietnamese restaurants in Boise, but we have been pleasantly surprised by Pho' Nuveau.  There food is absolutely AMAZING!  If you want fresh, authentic Vietnamese food, this is hands down the best in the entire Treasure Valley.  Their Salad rolls are perfect, and their Pho soups are delicious and wonderful.  We will be back very, very soon.
Pho-king delicious.
Good food, good service. We ate on the patio, so the atmosphere was great, too.
